description.plain:
Ckay (Real name Chukwuka Ekweani) is a multidiverse Artiste/Music Producer signed to the Africa’s biggest Music and Entertainment company; Chocolate City Music.

Ckay with his popular production tag “Ckay Yo” has produced songs for various artistes such as M.I Abaga, Dice Ailes, DJ Spinall, DJ Neptune, Ice Prince, IllBliss, Yung6ix, Moonchild Sanelly, Dremo, Zlatan and many more.

He released his first body of work, a 6 Track E.P titled “Who the Fxck is Ckay” in 2017 and has been coasting on a high ever since with various #1 records to his name such as Container, Nkechi e.t.c. Ckay’s sound and style is original and unique and he labels his genre of music “Afro-Futuristic”.

In 2019, Ckay dropped his second body of work titled Ckay The First creating much buzz and anticipation amongst fans & music lovers.

description.plain:
CKay partners with Moroccan rapper, ElGrandeToto, on the North African remix of his hit afrobeat love song “love nwantiti (ah ah ah)”.

The remix features a new verse, which sees both artists lamenting over the love and care of their dream partners, a prevalent theme throughout the entire song.
